TUNIS, Feb. 15 (Xinhua) -- Amid escalating tensions between Russia and Ukraine, the Tunisian Foreign Ministry confirmed on Tuesday that its embassy in Moscow of Russia has been in contact with the Tunisian community in Ukraine. "The Ukrainian authorities have assured that the situation in the country is normal and not worrying for the Tunisian community, in particular the students who continue their classes normally," the ministry said in a statement, adding that flights to and from Ukraine continue as usual. According to the statement, "no significant difficulties have been recorded regarding the situation of our community in Ukraine." "The ministry calls on all our citizens currently in this country (Ukraine) to communicate with our embassy in Moscow in order to update their data and report any difficulties they may encounter, in anticipation of any developments that may arise in the near future," it added.  â– 